<div class="row">
    <div class="col-md-3">
        <h2>This web application shows how to:</h2>
        <ul style="margin:0; padding:0">
            <li>Build an Identity Provider (IdP) compliant with standards</li>
            <li>Get a head start on <a href="https://www.eugdpr.org/">GDPR compliance</a> </li>
            <li>Meet the criteria for an <a href="http://openid.net/certification/"> OpenID certfied site</a></li>
            <li>Become an <a href="https://www.idefregistry.org/">IDEF Registered Site</a></li>
            <li>Built using <a href="http://docs.identityserver.io/en/release">IdentityServer4 </a>for OpenID Connect endpoint services</li>
            <li>Use this site's code available from <a href="https://github.com/TomCJones/idesg-idp"> open source on Github</a></li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="col-md-3">
        <h2>IDESG Guidelines</h2>
        <p>The collections of IDESG guidelines current at the time were used to create this example of best practices.</p>
        <p>
            <a class="btn btn-default" title="This link navigates to the IDESG wiki."
               href="https://wiki.idesg.org/wiki/index.php?title=User_Experience_Guidelines_Metrics">
                UX Guidelines &raquo;
            </a>
        </p>
        <p>
            The list of the baseline Functional requirments the IDEF version 1.0 are used in the Self-Assesment
            and are referenced in links throughout this example
            using the same azure coloring and mouse hover tool tip as the button below.
        </p>
        <p>
            <a class="btn btn-bfr" title="This link navigates to the main page for the web version of guidelines"
               href="https://wiki.idesg.org/wiki/index.php?title=Baseline_Functional_Requirements_v1.0">Baseline Functional Reqs &raquo;</a>
        </p>
        <div>
            Mapping of roles used from the IDEF:
            <ol>
                <li>Authenticate - This role is performed within this example for local users and in 3rd party providers if enabled.</li>
                <li>Authorize - This example, like all RPs, contain this role, some parts of which could be performed in other servers</li>
            </ol>
        </div>
    </div>
